summary:
Information was found on a printer that is in a public area with no VA Police security camera on it. dental, and audiology.
It was printed the morning of 8/29 at 7:47AM. It included fifty-six pages of patient clinic lists for the following clinics: dermatology, dialysis, metal health, eye, ears nose and throat, GI, pain, anesthesia, mental and audiology.  Incident Update
09/04/14:
The area was locked from the evening of Friday 8/29/14 through the morning of Tuesday 9/2/14, however there are several hours on Friday where the information was accessible.
09/12/14:
All 293 Veterans will receive letters offering credit protection services due to full SSN being potentially accessible.
